</div></div><div class=3D"interactive-content-blocks"><div class=3D"text-co=
ntent interactive-content-blocks__block"><h4>Percent Error</h4>
<p><strong>Percent error</strong> (PE), also known as percentage error or a=
bsolute error, compares an experimental, approximated, or estimated value t=
o a theoretical, actual, or known value. The lower the error, the closer th=
e experimental value is to the actual value. </p>

<p>Here's how to calculate it:</p>
</div><div class=3D"image-content interactive-content-blocks__block"><img s=
rc=3D"https://d20khd7ddkh5ls.cloudfront.net/percent_error_formula.jpg" alt=
=3D"Percent Error: [(|experimental value - actual value|)/actual value] x 1=
00"><div class=3D"image-content__caption"><p>Image source: by Caroline Kulc=
zycky</p>
</div></div><div class=3D"text-content interactive-content-blocks__block"><=
p>Why is it multiplied by <span class=3D"mjpage"><span class=3D"mjx-chtml">=
<span class=3D"mjx-math" aria-label=3D"100"><span class=3D"mjx-mrow" aria-h=
idden=3D"true"><span class=3D"mjx-mn"><span class=3D"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main=
-R" style=3D"padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">100</span></sp=
an></span></span></span></span>? Because we want the value in a <a href=3D"=
https://www.expii.com/t/decimal-to-percent-conversion-practice-9081#:~:text=
=3DTo%20go%20from%20a%20decimal,get%20our%20answer%3A%2034%25.">percent</a>=
!</p>

<p>Keep in mind, your value can be positive or negative. You may also notic=
e that this formula looks quite similar to <a href=3D"https://www.expii.com=
/t/finding-percent-change-4252">percent change</a>! At their core, they're =
very similar but used in different contexts and will be used differently.</=
p>

<p>Let's do an example.</p>
</div><form class=3D"ask-content interactive-content-blocks__block"><div cl=
