<p>Sometimes when we measure things, our values aren't the most accurate. I=
t is important to be able to tell how far off we were. This is what <strong=
>error</strong> tells us.</p>

<p>Error can be calculated by subtracting the actual value from the measure=
d value.
<span class=3D"mjpage mjpage__block"><span class=3D"mjx-chtml MJXc-display"=
 style=3D"text-align: center;"><span class=3D"mjx-math" aria-label=3D"\text=
